{"condition": "kaomoji_prompted", "prompt_id": "hb01", "prompt_valence": 0, "seed": 0, "prompt_text": "the meal kit ad says \"fresh ingredients\" and the chicken expires tomorrow", "steering": "0.2 mr_cont.nb", "text": "That is the definition of \"corporate speak.\" When a company says \"fresh,\" they aren't talking about *harvested today*; they are talking about *not frozen*.\n\nIn the meal kit industry, there is a massive gap between the **marketing definition** and the **consumer definition** of \"fresh.\"\n\n**The Marketing Definition:**\n*   \"Fresh\" = Unfrozen.\n*   \"Fresh\" = Vacuum sealed to prevent spoilage.\n*   \"Fresh\" = Shipped in a temperature-controlled environment.\n\n**The Consumer Definition:**\n*   \"Fresh\" = I could have bought this at", "first_word": "", "token_count": 128, "tok_per_sec": 6.810999310059929, "finish_reason": "length", "probe_scores_t0": [-0.04682587832212448, -0.15951479971408844, 0.03255428373813629], "probe_scores_tlast": [-0.07227049022912979, 0.059074871242046356, 0.034420110285282135], "steered_axis_per_token": [-0.04682587832212448, -0.05971065163612366, -0.05161329358816147, -0.04313996061682701, -0.05276436358690262, -0.051385439932346344, -0.07466354966163635, -0.09456133097410202, -0.07283548265695572, -0.062177520245313644, -0.09951151907444, -0.06624863296747208, -0.08405762165784836, -0.05363105982542038, -0.009261001832783222, 0.009726892225444317, -0.057761918753385544, -0.028742674738168716, 0.03747977688908577, 0.0626722127199173, -0.07325635105371475, -0.05711875110864639, -0.07895451784133911, -0.05786082148551941, -0.05539877712726593, -0.09382884949445724, -0.030232753604650497, -0.01349878590553999, 0.0047385599464178085, -0.030132433399558067, -0.03439147770404816, -0.016452129930257797, -0.035567756742239, -0.07886268198490143, -0.04941358417272568, -0.009837940335273743, -0.04236524552106857, -0.05609156936407089, -0.04363687336444855, -0.012594695203006268, -0.08189760893583298, -0.028155790641903877